The set $V = \{c_k \mid k \ge 1\}$ has density 1. The number of "holes" (positive integers not in $V$) is finite. Let $H = \mathbb{Z}^+ \setminus V$.
Since $c_k \ge 2$, $1 \in H$, so $|H| \ge 1$.
Let $b = |H|$. We will show this $b$ works.
For large $n$, the set $\{c_1, \dots, c_n\}$ roughly coincides with $V \cap \{1, \dots, n+b\}$.
Using the identity $\sum_{j=1}^n c_j = \sum_{y \in \{c_1,\dots,c_n\}} y$, we can relate $\sum_{j=1}^n a_j$ to $b$.
