The problem asks to prove the existence of $b$ and $N$ such that $|\sum_{j=m+1}^n (a_j - b)| \le 1007^2$.
Let $C = 2015$. Define $f(k) = k + a_k$. Since $1 \le a_k \le C$, $f$ is injective.
Let $H = \mathbb{Z}^+ \setminus \text{Im}(f)$ be the set of holes. Since $k+1 \le f(k) \le k+C$, the number of holes up to $x$ is bounded by $C$. Thus $H$ is finite. Let $b = |H|$. Since $1 \le f(k)-k$, $1 \in H$, so $b \ge 1$.
Let $N = \max H$. For $n \ge N$, the set of values $Z_n = \{ f(j) - n \mid j \le n, f(j) > n \}$ has size $b$ and is contained in $\{1, \dots, C\}$.
Moreover, for $n \ge N$, $n+1 \notin H \implies n+1 \in \text{Im}(f) \implies \exists j, f(j)=n+1$. This $j$ satisfies $j \le n$ and $f(j)-n=1$, so $1 \in Z_n$.
The sum $\sum_{j=m+1}^n (a_j - b)$ equals $\sum_{z \in Z_n} z - \sum_{z \in Z_m} z$.
Since $Z_n \subset \{1, \dots, C\}$, $|Z_n|=b$, and $1 \in Z_n$, the sum $\sum Z_n$ lies in an interval of length $(b-1)(C-b)$.
The maximum of $(b-1)(2015-b)$ is $1007^2$ (at $b=1008$).
This provides the required bound.

